To compile just type

make

To run pnfs from the local directory you must type 

make install

To provide a conventional "make install" type 

make deposit 

This will install to the directory /opt/pnfs.3.1.10/pnfs to set the instalation
prefix type the following

make deposit prefix=${YOUR_INSTALL_DIR}

where YOUR_INSTALL_DIR is the directory you want to install pnfs under.

To make a source tar ball for redistribution

make dist

To make an rpm type 

make rpm
